The paper deals with the random generation of words from a context-free language, which involves algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) for manipulating strings. The approach used is a multidimensional extension of Boltzmann samplers, which involves probability and statistics (cs.CG, cs.LG). The paper also discusses the generation of Tetris tessellations, which involves combinatorics (cs.DM) and computational complexity (cs.CC).
